sleeper buses sleeper buses are common in china; instead of seats they have bunk beds. these are a good way to cover longer distances — overnight at freeway speeds is 100 km or more — but they are not all that comfortable for large or tall travelers. generally, these are fast smooth and comfortable in the prosperous coastal provinces and less so in less developed areas. try to avoid getting the bunk at the very back of the bus; if the bus hits a major bump, passengers there become airborne. at some places you have to remove your shoes as 